# Next.js / React

- Use the **App Router** layout under **`apps/frontend/app/`** with `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` as appropriate.
- Prefer **named exports** for components when the file already follows that pattern; stay consistent with neighboring files.
- Keep frontend layer separation strict:
  - `.tsx` files are for view structure/composition.
  - `.ts` files are for reusable logic/helpers (formatters, selectors, mappers).
  - Web styles live in `.css`/`.module.css`.
- **Web UI**: Shared DOM components live in **`@portfolio/storybook`** (`packages/storybook/src/`). Import from the app as **`@portfolio/storybook`** (and package CSS subpaths). Do not add new `components/` for web UI; ESLint enforces this.
- **Presentational JSX belongs in Storybook**: **`apps/frontend/app/**/*.tsx`** route segments (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `global-error.tsx`, and any sibling view files) must be **pure composition** — import and render components from **`@portfolio/storybook`**, passing data/handlers as props. **Do not** render visible DOM primitives (**`h1`–`h6`**, **`p`**, **`button`**, **`label`**, **`ul`/`ol`/`li`/`dl`**, **`img`**, **`figure`**, **`blockquote`**, **`input`/`select`/`textarea`/`form`**) directly from these files. Structural/landmark elements (**`main`**, **`section`**, **`article`**, **`header`**, **`footer`**, **`nav`**, **`aside`**, **`div`**, **`span`**, **`html`**, **`body`**) **are** allowed for composition/layout and landmarks. Enforced by **`no-restricted-syntax`** in `apps/frontend/eslint.config.mjs`; if you find yourself reaching for a forbidden primitive, extract a new component into `packages/storybook/src/` (with a co-located story + `play`) and compose it from the app instead. If the component needs Next-specific behavior (e.g. `next/link`), accept it via a prop (see the **`SiteShellLinkComponent`** / **`linkComponent`** pattern).
- For **`apps/frontend/lib/cv-pdf/**`**, keep styles in react-pdf `StyleSheet` files (`styles.ts` / `styles/*.ts`) and do not migrate PDF styles to web CSS.
- **Data fetching**: Prefer server-side fetching in Server Components; use `fetch` caching defaults intentionally. For client mutations, use patterns already present in the repo (e.g. Server Actions, route handlers).
- **Metadata**: Use the Metadata API (`export const metadata` or `generateMetadata`) for SEO and social cards instead of ad-hoc `<head>` manipulation where possible.
- **Imports**: Use path aliases if `tsconfig` defines them; otherwise relative imports — match existing style.
- Run **`yarn lint`** and **`yarn build`** (or project-documented equivalents) after non-trivial changes; see skill `nextjs-change-checklist`.
